CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 11, 1959, pg. 1, reads: "As Pittsburgh Played Host to the All-Stars - Veterans - Two of the biggest stars in American League got together for a friendly chat before the annual All-Star game. One the left is Ted Williams, one of the game's greatest hitters, and on the right is Minnie Minoso, colorful outfielder with the Cleveland Indians. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Boston Red Sox baseball player Ted Williams and Cleveland Indians player Minnie Minoso, posed in dugout for 1959 All Star Game, Forbes Field
